      "label": "Condition",
      "value": "The paper has been folded fourteen times Along the papyrus fibresly and has a right margin of 2.5 cm. The top as well as the top and bottom left corners, and the bottom right corner have been torn off. On the left, bottom and right sides the original cutting lines have been preserved. In the top right corner there are some large lacunae that have damaged the text. Several small lacunae occur throughout the text.\nThe text on verso consists of nineteen lines written at a 180 degree angle compared to the recto in the same handwriting and it discusses the same subjects."
