    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Petition from someone calling himself \"slave\" (mamluk) complaining about a weak man (l. r1), someone \"who does not fear or convert from what he does\" (l. r4) and as someone who is full of evil and lies and posseses only little religion (l. v 4-5). The complaint concerns abuses that this man has subjected officials to amongst whom the sender of this letter from whom he confiscates money and part of the load from every boat that reaches him (ll. 5-7)."
    },
